flowchart TD
  A[Trigger: Weekly planning cadence start (scheduled job) or updated demand / supplier readiness feed for the upcoming weekly horizon.]
  A --> N1[Stream: STREAMS / Subject Areas - Ingest master orders, BOM, capacity, inventory, and supplier readiness into Subject Areas and STREAMS]
  N1 --> N2[Cortex: Process Builder - Rules + Data View - Run deterministic constraint evaluation and cost model to generate feasible schedule candidates]
  N2 --> N3{PB: Process Builder - Remote Functions - Transaction - Execute optimizer transaction (Remote Function) to pick cost-ranked schedule and lock resources}
  N3 -->|Primary| N4[PB: Remote Functions (ERP writeback) - Commit finalized schedule and supplier releases to SAP S/4HANA and create work orders]
  N4 --> N5[UI: UI Screens + CWB Lifecycle (Notification) - Surface schedule summary and KPIs; route any flagged exceptions to CWB Lifecycle for planner review]
  N5 --> N6[PB: Subject Areas - Dashboard (UI Screens) - Post-execution review and monitoring of realized COGS and OTIF metrics]
  N6 --> Z1[Outcome: Lowered COGS through optimized sequencing and allocation, improved line efficiency (reduced changeover / downtime), higher on-time delivery rates, fewer supplier release errors, and reduced manual schedule rework.]
  N3 -->|Critical supplier shortfall or confir...| B1[Generate exception CWB with prioritized mitigation options (alternate supplier, re-allocation, defer builds) and invoke dynamic subprocess to simulate contingency schedules.]
  B1 --> O1[Outcome: Planners receive structured options for manual decision; system retains the best contingency plan to minimize COGS impact and maintain OTIF where possible.]
  O1 --> End[End]
  N3 -->|Optimizer/Remote Function fails or re...| B2[Fallback to deterministic rule-based reserve schedule generated by Process Builder Rules and notify planners with error details and suggested manual schedule.]
  B2 --> O2[Outcome: A safe, rule-compliant schedule is available to commit to ERP to avoid missing supplier release windows while engineering resolves optimizer issue.]
  O2 --> End[End]
  N3 -->|Multiple near-equal cost schedules wi...| B3[Surface top-ranked alternatives with cost vs. OTIF trade-offs in UI Screen and create Action Item for planner sign-off; allow automated tie-breaker policy if SLA allows.]
  B3 --> O3[Outcome: Planner selects preferred trade-off quickly; chosen schedule is committed and lower-impact alternatives are saved for rapid rollback if needed.]
  O3 --> End[End]
  Z1 --> End[End]